John Cowan writes:
  &quot;intelligibility across accent boundaries&quot;

I see &quot;intelligibility across accent boundaries&quot; as one of 2 big 
problems selling QS to people who really aren&#39;t into this , as we are. 
They are:
1. The intelligibility problem has already been solved by TO.  It&#39;s 
standard.
2. Writing (unsanctioned) phonetic English is considered uneducated or 
just plain stupid.

The average person is likely to ask why we should even bother with QS as 
general solution for the Anglophone world, or at all?

Vin
